  "instructions": [
    "Rinse the corn kernels and set them aside to drain.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until it is translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute.",
    "Add the diced red bell pepper and cook until it is tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the diced tomato and cook until it is tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the corn kernels, white wine, vegetable broth, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper to the saucepan.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, until the liquid is absorbed and the corn is tender, about 20 minutes.",
    "Fluff the pilaf with a fork and serve hot."
